description: The latest round of Gaza cease-fire talks ended in Cairo. Meanwhile, Israel closed its main crossing point for delivering badly needed humanitarian aid for Gaza after Hamas attacked it.
title: Hamas says latest cease-fire talks have ended. Israel vows a military operation soon

description: The English actor played Captain Edward John Smith in the 1997 film Titanic as well as King Théoden of Rohan in The Lord of the Rings trilogy.
title: Bernard Hill, who starred in 'Titanic' and 'The Lord of the Rings,' dies at 79

description: Sotheby's June 26 auction of Thomas Taylor's watercolor illustration for Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone is estimated to sell for $400,000-$600,000.
title: The original 'Harry Potter' book cover art is expected to break records at auction

description: President Volodymyr Zelenskyy urged Ukrainians in an Easter address to be united in prayer and called God an "ally" in the war with Russia.
title: Ukraine's Zelenskyy calls God an "ally" against Russia in Orthodox Easter message

description: Three bodies recovered in an area of Mexico's Baja California state are likely to be those of two Australians and an American who went missing last weekend during a camping trip, officials said.
title: Bodies found in Mexico likely those of missing American and two Australians

description: While most buildings in Israel are required to have bomb shelters, a zoning catch-22 has left Bedouin villagers unprotected.
title: When rockets fall, some Israeli citizens have nowhere to hide

description: A driver died after a vehicle crashed into a gate at the White House Saturday night, but the fatal collision is being investigated "only as a traffic crash", law enforcement authorities said.
title: Driver dies after crashing into White House perimeter gate, Secret Service says
